      "message": "I may be misunderstanding the comment, but I think this sets up a 2 pixel overlap (although differently for horizontal and vertical):\n\nTo show my thought, adjacent subrows are shown on two separate lines to show where overlap would be.\nNo overlap:                    |****\n                               |    ****\n                               |        ****\nMy interpretation of comment:  |*****\n                               |    *****\n                               |        *****\nMy understanding of code:     |******\n                              |    ******\n                              |        ******\n\nSince it\u0027s not y*tileH-1, the column overlap is different currently, and looks like this (transposed):\n                               |******\n                               |    ******\n                               |         ****** \n                               |            ******\nAnd in this case, the overlap for columns is actually changing per-column.\n\nI think the way to do this is just \"x * tileW, y * tileH, tileW + 1, tileH + 1\" to get a single pixel of overlap.  Or \"x * tileW - 1, y * tileH - 1, tileW + 2, tileH + 2\" to have each tile overlap onto a single original pixel of its neighbors (for a total of 2 if you count that tile\u0027s own extension).",
